{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place water, 1 tsp salt and olive oil in mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket and add basmati rice to it.","Insert Varoma tray in Varoma dish. Grease Varoma tray with olive oil, place salmon fillets on it and season with ½ tsp salt and black pepper. Set Varoma in position and steam <b>15-17 min\/Varoma\/speed 4<b>. Set covered Varoma aside on a plate to keep salmon warm. Remove simmering basket using spatula and set aside. Empty and rinse mixing bowl.","Place onions and garlic clove in mixing bowl then chop <strong><b>5 sec\/speed 5<b><\/strong>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl using spatula.","Add butter and sauté <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add cream, vegetable stock paste, tomato purée, dill, chilli flakes and cornflour then heat <strong><b>5 min\/98°C\/speed 1.5<b><\/strong>. Serve salmon and rice immediately with sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1000 g water","1 ½ tsp salt","20 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing","250 g basmati rice","4 fresh salmon fillets, skinless (125 g each)","¼ tsp ground black pepper","60 g onions, halved","1 garlic clove","10 g butter","400 g cream, 35-37 % fat","2 heaped tsp vegetable stock paste, homemade","1 ½ tbsp tomato purée (concentrated)","2 sprigs fresh dill, leaves only, chopped","1 - 2 pinches dried chilli flakes, to taste (optional)","1 tsp cornflour (starch)"]}],"id":"r131940","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-uESyyCN5Avg\/XZVQWe-vlZI\/AAAAAAAAdAI\/XHbY7plZ_3shC62uPSU62oleonwe2H5pACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_LAnsZRiMPiPN3sIk.png","title":"Salmon and Basmati Rice with Dill Cream Sauce","publishedAt":"2016-09-26T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"34 g","fat":"55 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"53 g","calories":"3569 kJ \/ 853 kcal"},"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","4 portions"]}